sentences: Robert Earl "Kool" Bell (born October 8, 1950), also known by his Muslim name Muhammad Bayyan, is an American musician, singer and songwriter.
Along with his brother, Ronald Bell, he began playing jazz, and in 1964 they formed a group named the "Jazziacs".
They began playing at clubs in New York City under a series of different band names before settling on the name "Kool & the Gang" in 1968.
He was one of the co-writers of the song "Boardmeeting" from the 2007 album Timbaland Presents Shock Value.
